track_notes: As you can see, we made a mistake at the beginning of our walk to summit; there is a car park with plenty room if you come early. The path is easy, the summit is croyded, so you can set up the antenna on a small hill beside.
This track is a bit long, but nicer than the regular way! Of course not to be done in winter because of the snow

The access to the car park is depending of the snow. If the road is closed it could be a very long walk with snowshoes. you may need crampons if there is ice for some part of the path is very sloope. Nice view on summit and much place for antenna
We went on summit with all the familly... not interessted by radio or antennas!
